e reviewing and catching up before they can \nmove on.\n  Every year in May, Books for Keeps sends kids off to summer vacation \narmed with a variety of titles tailored to their interests to entertain \nand challenge them over the break. We have Melaney Smith from Athens, \nGeorgia, to thank for her initiative to encourage literacy and to \ninspire students.\n\n                          ____________________\n\n\n\n    ", "day": "16"}, {"url": "http://www.congress.gov/congressional-record/2015/11/16/house-section/article/H8158-4", "month": "11", "year": "2015", "originaltext": "\n        \n\n[Page H8158]\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [www.gpo.gov]\n\n\n\n\n               COMMUNICATION FROM THE CLERK OF THE HOUSE\n\n  The SPEAKER pro tempore (Mr. Woodall) laid before the House the \nfollowing communication from the Clerk of the House of Representatives:\n\n                                              Office of the Clerk,\n\n\n                                     House of Representatives,\n\n                                 Washington, DC, November 5, 2015.\n     Hon. Paul D. Ryan,\n     The Speaker, U.S. Capitol,\n     House of Representatives, Washington, DC.\n       Dear Mr. Speaker: Pursuant to the permission granted in \n     Clause 2(h) of Rule II of the Rules of the U.S. House of \n     Representatives, the Clerk received the following message \n     from the Secretary of the Senate on November 5, 2015 at 2:05 \n     p.m.:\n       That the Senate agreed to S.J. Res. 22.\n       With best wishes, I am\n           Sincerely,\n     Karen L. Haas.\n\n                          ____________________\n\n\n\n    ", "day": "16"}, {"url": "http://www.congress.gov/congressional-record/2015/11/16/house-section/article/H8158-5", "month": "11", "year": "2015", "originaltext": "\n        \n\n[Page H8158]\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [www.gpo.gov]\n\n\n\n\n               COMMUNICA