e submitted regarding the \nspecific powers granted to Congress in the Constitution to enact the \naccompanying bill or joint resolution.\n\n\n\n    ", "day": "16"}, {"url": "http://www.congress.gov/congressional-record/2015/11/16/house-section/article/H8240-3", "month": "11", "year": "2015", "originaltext": "\n        \n\n[Page H8240]\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [www.gpo.gov]\n\n            By Mr. SHUSTER:\n       H.R. 3996.\n       Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuant \n     to the following:\n       Article I, Section 8 of the United States Constitution, \n     specifically Clause 1 (related to laying and collecting \n     Taxes, and providing for the common defense and general \n     Welfare of the United States), Clause 3 (related to \n     regulation of Commerce with foreign Nations, and among the \n     several States, and with Indian Tribes), and Clause 7 \n     (related to establishment of Post Offices and Post Roads).\n\n\n\n    ", "day": "16"}, {"url": "http://www.congress.gov/congressional-record/2015/11/16/house-section/article/H8240-4", "month": "11", "year": "2015", "originaltext": "\n        \n\n[Page H8240]\nFrom the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [www.gpo.gov]\n\n            By Mr. CUMMINGS:\n       H.R. 3997.\n       Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuant \n     to the following:\n       Article I, Section 8: The Congress shall have Power to . . \n     . provide for the common defense and general Welfare of the \n     United States;\n       Article I, Section 8, Clause 18: To make all Laws which \n     shall be necessary and proper for carrying into Execution the \n     foregoing Powers.\n\n\n\n    ", "day": "16"}, {"url": "http://www.congress.gov/congressional-record/2015/11/16/house-section/article/H8240-5", "month": "11", "year": "2015", "originaltext": "\n        \n\n[Page H8240]\nFrom the Congressional Record Online